<P>There are &s;ome Per&s;ons made &s;o by <HI>Nature,</HI> that
they are <HI>&s;low, dark, gloomy, joyle&s;s, puzzling,</HI> and <HI>per|plexing,</HI>
and they pa&s;s for the wi&s;e, prudent, guarded
Men of the <HI>World:</HI> They may attack <HI>Error,</HI> but &s;el|dom
<PB N="22" REF="26">
find out <HI>Truth</HI> by them&s;elves; like the <HI>Scuttle|fi&s;h,</HI>
they &s;pout out their own <HI>black Liquor</HI> on the <HI>pellu|cid
Element.</HI> If they are <HI>hone&s;t</HI> and <HI>&s;incere,</HI> they are
much to be pitied, and are to be treated with <HI>Huma|nity</HI>
and <HI>Charity,</HI> being in the State of tho&s;e born <HI>poor</HI>
and <HI>blind,</HI> and &s;o de&s;titute of the Nece&s;&s;aries and Con|veniences
of Life. They mu&s;t do the be&s;t they can,
and be charitably &s;upplied, and with Docility be wil|ling
