he <HI>a&s;cended</HI> into it, even into the Child's Diet.</P>
<P>XIV. He that is <HI>old</HI> when he is young, that is,
treats him&s;elf as a wi&s;e <HI>old Man</HI> does, or ought to do,
by great <HI>Temperance, Air</HI> and <HI>Exerci&s;e,</HI> if he lives pa&s;t
